//Assignment 2
Q. Write down the steps to configure ip address of Linux Machine
Ans. Following steps are used to configure IP Address of a linux machine
  1. To check IP Address - ifconfig
  2. Ro start/stop/restart network - service network start|stop|restart
  3. To set network IP Address- ifconfig eth0 <IP Address> netmask 255.255.255.0
  4. To check communication between two nodes - ping <IP Address>
                                              - ping -c 10 <IP Address>
  5. Clearing IP Tables - iptables -F
  6. To enable/disable Ethernet(NIC) card - ifconfig eth0 up|down
